Context:
George Brown College offers hands-on learning experiences for students under faculty and industry professional supervision. The college has affordable services in various locations:

1. The Chefs' House (215 King St. E): A live restaurant environment where hospitality and culinary arts students practice their skills. Open for lunch from 11:30 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. and dinner from 5:30 p.m. to 8:30 p.m. Follow on Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram @thechefshouse.

2. George Brown Cafe (300 Adelaide St. E, second floor): Open Monday to Friday, 7:30 a.m. to 2 p.m., excluding holidays. Follow on Instagram @georgebrowncafe and Twitter @GBCCafe.

3. Chef on the Run (300 Adelaide St. E, main floor): Open Tuesdays to Fridays from 11 a.m. to 2 p.m. Sell freshly prepared meals, desserts, and products. Follow on Instagram @chefontherungbc and Twitter @GBCcotr.

The college also operates several childcare centres across the Greater Toronto Area staffed by fully trained early childhood educators. Some notable ones include George Brown’s Casa Loma Child Care Centre and other lab school childcare centres operated by the college. They provide meaningful learning opportunities for students and high-quality childcare services to children and families.

The offerings at Chef on the Run can be checked by dialing 416-415-5000 x 2515.

Context:
The college operates lab school childcare centres in accordance with Ontario's Ministry of Education and public health measures. For more information, visit the Child Care Centres page.

The WAVE Clinics offer affordable dental services to the public. More information about services, fees, registration, and COVID-19 protocols can be found on the WAVE Dental Clinic page.

Local non-profit organizations can receive graphic design help from senior students at the School of Design. Contact Ana Rita Morais or Lori Endes for more information.

The IN Store sells student-designed products, including home décor items, tote bags, notebooks, refillable water bottles, and more. Visit instoregbc.com for more information.

The School of Makeup and Esthetics provides a wide variety of spa services at affordable prices. Call (416) 415-5000 ext. 4070 to book an appointment.

Students in their final year of the Theatre Arts – Performance program present productions from November to April at the Young Centre for the Performing Arts. More information about upcoming shows can be found on the website.

The contact details for George Brown College are: 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, ask.george@georgebrown.ca, and social media hub.
